      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "WHOA NELLIE (3) is back after a break of five months. Closed strongly at her second race start with an encouraging second over 1350m at Beaumont (Newcastle) last December. Fitted with the two good trials and the nose roll comes off. Can finish over the top of these. HOLD MY DRINK (1) from an in-form yard and ready to peak third-up. Nailed late over 1200m at the Sapphire Coast first-up, then failed to close off with a disappointing fifth over 1205m at the Sapphire Coast. Raced flat last start and can bounce back today. POPULISM (6) eight weeks between runs at just her second start when struck trouble early and got further back than expected to finish fifth over 1200m at Gosford. Worth another chance from the low draw. WHAT A GENT (8) stalked the speed first-up before he faded in the straight when no match for Mrs Maree over 1200m at Wyong. Can keep improving as he gets out in trip.",
